contentrichtext.text: '''Whitsunday''' may be: '''Days''': * The Sunday of the feast of [[Whitsun]] or [[Pentecost]] in the Christian liturgical year, observed 7 weeks after Easter * One of the Scottish [[quarter days]], always falling on 15 May '''Places''': * The [[Electoral district of Whitsunday]] * [[Whitsunday Island]], the largest of the Whitsunday Islands * The [[Whitsunday Islands]], Queensland, Australia * The [[Whitsunday Regional Council]] (including former [[Shire of Whitsunday]]) ==References== {{reflist}} {{disambig}}
